## Traps

- Tests: `ENVOY_KEYRING=memory uv run --no-sync pytest …`. CI = py3.11+3.13. `.python-version` pinned 3.13.
- **F12-b bridge thread-affinity:** `run_coro_blocking` runs the async revoke on a fresh WORKER thread per call (deliberate — makes it re-entrant + loop-safe; a shared executor would deadlock on re-entrancy). stdlib `sqlite3` is thread-affine, so any code driving the bridge MUST pass a FRESH / lazily-initialised `TrustStoreAdapter` (let the worker thread `initialize()` it), NEVER a pre-initialised one. Tests seed via a throwaway `asyncio.run` (persists to the on-disk vault) then drive the sync facade; cleanup is `run_coro_blocking(store.close())` in a `finally` (verify with `-W error::ResourceWarning`).
- **F12-c precondition (security-reviewer MED-3):** before wiring `revoke_prior_grant` to a real `envoy grant revoke` CLI, EITHER drive a fresh adapter through the bridge (tested-safe) OR move the kailash chain/posture sub-stores to per-operation connections (the `store.py:944-956` bc/digest precedent). A pre-initialised adapter + the bridge = cross-thread `sqlite3` reuse → `ProgrammingError` or silent no-op write (retained authority).
- Keychain: thread ONE backend into EVERY consumer; SessionRouter loads TWO keychain keys (signing + encryption). Cross-process CLI tests MUST share one backend (`ENVOY_KEYRING=memory` mints a fresh dict per `resolve_keyring_backend()` call).
- "Buildable" MUST be verified EMPIRICALLY — S6a/S6b/S6c/S5o-enc/S4g-2 ALL drifted. Check the real consumer, not the todo's claim. (S4g-2b's "multi-adapter Genesis" framing was also an over-statement — the spec mandates breadth-3 root+3-children, single adapter.)
- WS-6 shards SAME-class serialized (runtime.py/store) — never worktree-parallelize within WS-6.
- admin-merge: docs PRs path-skip the matrix; code PRs run py3.11/py3.13 (`gh pr checks <N> --watch`).
